                type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On April 2, <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">General Eisenhower</persName>, in
                    a letter to Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_LOVETTRA1"
                        >Lovett</persName>, asked to be relieved as Supreme Allied Commander,
                    Europe. Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LOVETTRA1">Lovett</persName> replied on
                    April 8 that he was initiating the appropriate action to secure <persName
                        corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">General Eisenhower</persName>’s release, effective
                    June 1. On April 28, President Truman announced that General <persName
                        corresp="#p_RIDGWAYMB1">Matthew B. Ridgway</persName> had been appointed to
                    succeed <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">General Eisenhower</persName>. For
                    the text of the letters exchanged by <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">General
                        Eisenhower</persName> and Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LOVETTRA1"
                        >Lovett</persName>, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                    April 21, 1952, page 614. For the text of the statement by President Truman, see
                        <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, May 12, 1952, page 743.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
